The land allotted the Lady being ſold for 7800 l. with 6500 l. thereof Barne-Elmes was purchaſed, but Sir John being truſted by the Lady to go to Mr, Stephens to draw the Conveyance. went to other Councel, and in the Clauſe where it ſhould be freely at the Lady's diſpoſal, ſolely without Sir John;
• he cauſed to be inſerted theſe words, that the Lady ſhould have power to convey the ſame to ſuch intents and
purpoſes, as by the ſaid Elizabeth ſolely, and without the ſaid Sir John Kennedy by writing under her hand and Seal enrolled, ſhould be limited and appointed; wherein beſides the contradictorineſs of the ſenſe he cauſed in that Deed delivered the Lady (the more to blind her Eyes) Enrolled to be raſed and made Indented Deed. 31. December 3d. Jac. 8.
